<h1>Problem 605 - 2016 IMOSL, C3, CG</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer relatively prime to \(6\). We paint the vertices of a regular \(n\)-gon with three colours so that there is an odd number of vertices of each colour. Show that there exists an isosceles triangle whose three vertices are of different colours.</p>
